        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 10:14AM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 1014 AM EDT, trained weather spotters reported a strong
thunderstorm near Mishawaka, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lakeville, Benton, New Paris, Woodland, Jimtown, Southwest, Osceola,
Elkhart, Foraker, Dunlap, Mishawaka, Wakarusa, Middlebury, Goshen,
Waterford Mills, Wyatt, Gulivoire Park, Granger, and South Bend.

This includes Interstate 80 in Indiana between mile markers 85 and
91.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
